h to evaluate the radically different policies they pursue. This is a book for a world in which bold cities are collaborating to combat climate change and inspire hope for democracy even as reactionary populists take over national governments in the United States and Europe. It calls for a new social contract among citizens and municipalities to secure not only their sustainability but their survival.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCities and townsxGrowth. 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspects. 0aGlobal warming. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022811340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300228113423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300228113/original  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles